{
  "info": {
    "_postman_id": "a1b2c3d4-e5f6-7890-abcd-ef1234567890",
    "name": "Task Management API",
    "description": "Postman collection for the Task Management API (NestJS).\n\n## Setup\n1. Import this collection into Postman.\n2. Ensure the API is running (`npm run start:dev`) and PostgreSQL/Redis are up.\n3. Default `baseUrl` is `http://localhost:3000` (matches `PORT` in `.env`).\n\n## Suggested flow\n1. **Register** → **Login** (tokens saved automatically)\n2. **Get Current User** or **Update Profile**\n3. **Create Project** → **List Projects** → **Get Project** → **Update Project**\n4. **Refresh Token** when the access token expires (15m default)\n5. **Logout** when done\n\n## Rate limits\n- Global: 100 requests / 60s\n- Auth routes (`/auth/*`): 5 requests / 60s\n\n## Authorization\n- Collection-level Bearer auth uses `{{accessToken}}`\n- `USER` role: own projects only\n- `ADMIN` role: all projects",
    "schema": "https://schema.getpostman.com/json/collection/v2.1.0/collection.json"
  },
  "auth": {
    "type": "bearer",
    "bearer": [
      {
        "key": "token",
        "value": "{{accessToken}}",
        "type": "string"
      }
    ]
  },
  "variable": [
